#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:101
msgid "DTM filter (slope-based)"
msgstr "DMT filter (zasnovan na nagibu)"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:102
msgid "``Added in 3.34``"
msgstr "``Dodato u 3.34``"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:104
msgid ""
"Can be used to filter a digital elevation model in order to classify its "
"cells into ground and object (non-ground) cells."
msgstr ""
"Može se koristiti za filtriranje digitalnog modela visina radi "
"klasifikovanja njegovih ćelija na ćelije tla i objekata (koje nisu tlo)."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:106
msgid ""
"The tool uses concepts as described by Vosselman (2000) and is based on the "
"assumption that a large height difference between two nearby cells is "
"unlikely to be caused by a steep slope in the terrain. The probability that "
"the higher cell might be non-ground increases when the distance between the "
"two cells decreases. Therefore the filter defines a maximum height "
"difference (``dz_max``) between two cells as a function of the distance "
"(``d``) between the cells (``dz_max( d ) = d``). A cell is classified as "
"terrain if there is no cell within the kernel radius to which the height "
"difference is larger than the allowed maximum height difference at the "
"distance between these two cells."
msgstr ""
"Alat koristi koncepte kako ih je opisao Vosselman (2000) i zasniva se na "
"pretpostavci da veliku razliku u visini između dve bliske ćelije verovatno "
"ne izaziva strm nagib terena. Verovatnoća da viša ćelija ne pripada tlu "
"raste kako se rastojanje između dve ćelije smanjuje. Zato filter definiše "
"maksimalnu razliku visine (``dz_max``) između dve ćelije kao funkciju "
"rastojanja (``d``) između ćelija (``dz_max( d ) = d``). Ćelija se "
"klasifikuje kao teren ako unutar poluprečnika jezgra nema ćelije prema kojoj"
" je razlika visine veća od dozvoljene maksimalne razlike visine na "
"rastojanju između te dve ćelije."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:113
#, python-format
msgid ""
"The approximate terrain slope (``s``) parameter is used to modify the filter"
" function to match the overall slope in the study area (``dz_max( d ) = d * "
"s``). A 5 % confidence interval (``ci = 1.65 * sqrt( 2 * stddev )``) may be "
"used to modify the filter function even further by either relaxing "
"(``dz_max( d ) = d * s + ci``) or amplifying (``dz_max( d ) = d * s - ci``) "
"the filter criterium."
msgstr ""
"Parametar približnog nagiba terena (``s``) koristi se za izmenu funkcije "
"filtera radi usklađivanja sa ukupnim nagibom u oblasti proučavanja "
"(``dz_max( d ) = d * s``). Interval poverenja od 5 % (``ci = 1.65 * sqrt( 2 "
"* stddev )``) može se koristiti za dalju izmenu funkcije filtera, bilo "
"ublažavanjem (``dz_max( d ) = d * s + ci``) ili pojačavanjem (``dz_max( d ) "
"= d * s - ci``) kriterijuma filtera."

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:118
msgid ""
"*References: Vosselman, G. (2000): Slope based filtering of laser altimetry "
"data. IAPRS, Vol. XXXIII, Part B3, Amsterdam, The Netherlands, 935-942*"
msgstr ""
"*Reference: Vosselman, G. (2000): Slope based filtering of laser altimetry "
"data. IAPRS, Vol. XXXIII, Part B3, Amsterdam, The Netherlands, 935-942*"

#: ../../docs/user_manual/processing_algs/qgis/rasterterrainanalysis.rst:121
